<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Monster Camping</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Kurgann">Kurgann</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:48 p.m. 29/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Monster Camping<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>As stated in a previous post, I am a barbarian warrior. I am currently at the fifteenth level. I have a slight problem with "camping" at spawn places in wait for that big creature with the great item. Generally I do not find camping a problem, I think it's a fair deal, I have done it many times myself with the elite ledge in BlackBurrow. My one problem is that many people want, perhaps need that great rare item. All good and fine if you are getting that item to use, but if it's just for profit, then it's a problem. People auction off the great loot or sell it in-town, where prices are even worse to those who wish to purchase something. I ask that to gain money, simply kill and loot normally, and do not "camp" for items unless you plan to actually use them. At level fifteen, many monsters that I meet can only be hit by magic or magical weapons. Combine weapons are quite expensive. I wish to find a bone bladed claymore at Befallen. I know you get it off a troll shadow knight, I also know he is heavily camped. Not just for me, but for all the players in need out there, I plead campers who still wish to kill the creature for experience donate the item to a player who came to use it. It is not fair that someone cannot gain a usefull item just because the money-hungry high-leveled guy wants to gain the item purely for profit. I do hope people will take heed of this message so players across Norath will have a better and easier time trying to gain items to further their fun and adventuring. Thank you.

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
